{
  "texts": [
    "Compared with two-stream convolution, 3D convolution is faster and more efficient.",
    "However, the existing network cannot make full use of video temporal and spatial characteristics, and the recognition rate is low.",
    "Therefore, feature extraction methods for human action recognition still need to be optimized.",
    "RNNs can be used to analyze temporal data due to recursive joins in its hidden layer.",
    "However, traditional RNNs have the problem of disappearing gradients, and cannot effectively model long time series."
  ]
}